1
00:00:00,370 --> 00:00:02,170
(All characters, locations,
organizations, and incidents...)

2
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:03,680
(in this drama are fictional.)

3
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:05,180
(This production followed
all guidelines for young actors.)

4
00:00:06,580 --> 00:00:07,950
What's your blood type?

5
00:00:08,610 --> 00:00:09,650
Took you long enough to ask.

6
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:11,250
I'm type A.

7
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:15,320
But your father is B-negative.

8
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:19,590
Does that mean
your biological mother was type AB?

9
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:24,400
Why the sudden obsession
with blood types?

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,370
Wait, are you Rh-negative?

11
00:00:28,170 --> 00:00:29,170
No.

12
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,940
You think Young Chae is trying to...

13
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,870
get a DNA test on Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon?

14
00:01:11,610 --> 00:01:12,610
I'm positive.

15
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,050
(Episode 88)

16
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:29,760
I need to get a DNA test done
on Jin Tae Seok and Se Hoon.

17
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:32,730
Is there a reason for that?

18
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:35,800
Joo Young Chae is trying to get...

19
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:39,000
a DNA paternity test between Se Hoon
and Jin Tae Seok.

20
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:43,610
She must have
a reason for it, right?

21
00:01:44,710 --> 00:01:45,710
Understood.

22
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:51,950
What are you talking about?

23
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:56,220
There's a chance Se Hoon isn't
Jin Tae Seok's biological son?

24
00:01:58,020 --> 00:01:59,120
If that's true,

25
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:02,030
does this change
how we get our revenge?

26
00:02:07,470 --> 00:02:10,700
(Korea Bio-Genetics Center)

27
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,040
This is what it says?

28
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:18,810
Are you sure this is real?

29
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:20,880
You didn't switch them or anything,
did you?

30
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:23,010
Do you think I'm like you?
I don't go around switching things.

31
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,250
Oh, my.

32
00:02:26,990 --> 00:02:29,020
Ms. Young Chae would never
do such a thing.

33
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,720
"Ms.?" My foot. She's married.

34
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,190
Then what should I call her?

35
00:02:33,630 --> 00:02:35,290
- Young Chae?
- Madam.

36
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:41,230
- How dare you?
- I need to use the bathroom.

37
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,540
Right. When you have to go,
you should.

38
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:49,170
(There is a 99.998 percent chance
of a biological relationship...)

39
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:50,170
(between Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon.)

40
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:55,450
That's strange.
My gut is never wrong.

41
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:59,880
(Chairman Han Hye Ra)

42
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,460
(There is a 0.123 percent chance
of a biological relationship...)

43
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:08,790
(between Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon.)

44
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,530
How can this be?

45
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:21,870
Can we really trust these results?

46
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:24,380
Manager Hwang
picked them up himself.

47
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,140
What should we do now?

48
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:29,750
Until now, I thought Se Hoon
was the heir to Kunhyang Group.

49
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:33,890
To be honest, I planned to
use you, Vice Chairman Joo,

50
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,090
to motivate Se Hoon.

51
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:36,990
I figured as much.

52
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,220
Now, I need to change my plans.

53
00:03:41,490 --> 00:03:42,960
Kunhyang Group...

54
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:46,300
is no longer run by Jin Tae Seok.
I, Han Hye Ra, am now in charge.

55
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,730
And my bloodline...

56
00:03:50,570 --> 00:03:52,200
will be the ones
to inherit Kunhyang Group.

57
00:03:53,670 --> 00:03:55,040
It's too soon.

58
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:58,080
- I'm not ready.
- I'll help you.

59
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,980
You can grow into the role.

60
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:01,750
We can worry about that later.

61
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:07,350
For now, let's focus on taking down
Jin Tae Seok, one step at a time.

62
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:08,520
Of course.

63
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:11,790
Did you file for a retrial?

64
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:15,590
When does the trial start?

65
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,570
She's not answering her phone
or at her desk.

66
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,200
(Chairman Han Hye Ra)

67
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:32,280
What brings you here,
Honorary Chairman?

68
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:34,010
Cha Jung Won filed for a retrial.

69
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:37,680
- You mean the Joo Sang Cheol case?
- She'll clear Cha Ki Beom's name.

70
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,480
Do you think she has any evidence?

71
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,890
There's no way she has any evidence.

72
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:44,390
What about the audio file
from the board meeting?

73
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:47,330
An audio recording with no visuals
isn't definitive proof.

74
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:50,930
What on earth did they use
to file for a retrial?

75
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,300
It's clear Chairman Han is helping
Cha Jung Won behind the scenes.

76
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:58,400
What's the point of proving
a dead man's innocence?

77
00:05:02,170 --> 00:05:03,170
What's going on here?

78
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:05,980
Why is there a father-son bonding session
in my office...

79
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:07,350
when the chairman herself is away?

80
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,560
(Vice President Jin Se Hoon)

81
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:25,130
Don't just barge into my office
without calling first.

82
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:41,110
(There is a 99.998 percent chance
of a biological relationship...)

83
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:42,350
(between Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon.)

84
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,280
The truth doesn't matter.

85
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:49,220
Se Hoon has to be
the heir to Kunhyang Group.

86
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,990
That's the only way I...

87
00:05:52,090 --> 00:05:53,730
can become the lady of Kunhyang.

88
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,200
You know there's a fashion show
next week, right?

89
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,630
I know.

90
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,940
The designers are modeling it
themselves, right?

91
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,970
I'm the main event.
You have to be there.

92
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:09,770
Of course. I'm the vice president
of the group, after all.

93
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,140
That's not what I mean.

94
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,110
I was hoping you'd come
to cheer on your wife.

95
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:18,750
- Did you have lunch?
- Not yet.

96
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:21,150
Let's go.

97
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:22,520
Okay.

98
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,560
I'm asking you a question.

99
00:06:29,930 --> 00:06:32,060
Why did Cha Jung Won
file for a retrial?

100
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,930
You really don't know why?

101
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:38,570
Ki Beom was wrongfully convicted
of Joo Sang Cheol's murder.

102
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,440
She wants to clear his name.

103
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:42,110
What good will that do now?

104
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:44,380
Have you forgotten
what Ki Beom means to Jung Won?

105
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,980
I'm her flesh and blood.
Not Cha Ki Beom.

106
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:50,650
I am Jung Won's father.

107
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,820
But you said you weren't
the real killer, right?

108
00:06:58,690 --> 00:06:59,960
Then it shouldn't matter
to you, right?

109
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:04,700
She's trying to restore the honor
of the man who raised her,

110
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,260
and I want to help her.

111
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:10,030
And I trust you feel the same way.

112
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,810
Of course I do.

113
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:20,980
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

114
00:07:26,950 --> 00:07:28,620
I don't have to serve
the likes of you.

115
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,390
Excuse me? We're paying customers.

116
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:35,190
Fine, since you're already here,
eat up and get out fast...

117
00:07:35,390 --> 00:07:37,090
before I smack you both
with a piece of meat.

118
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,530
Of all places, why here?

119
00:07:40,670 --> 00:07:42,730
The person I'm meeting
wanted to come here.

120
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:46,040
What? I thought this was
just a date for the two of us.

121
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,810
You wanted to see me?

122
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,080
If you're done eating, you can go.

123
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:08,430
I heard Cha Jung Won decided
to file for a retrial.

124
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,800
By any chance,
you're not the one planning...

125
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:14,230
to testify as a witness, are you?

126
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:18,570
Why would that interest you,
Vice President Jin?

127
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,770
Why do you think?

128
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:23,110
If Cha Ki Beom is found
innocent in the retrial,

129
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:25,210
then the real killer
will also be revealed.

130
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,810
Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok
is the real killer.

131
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:29,850
You know that, and you're still
going to go through with this?

132
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:34,150
- Do you have more than one life?
- Okay, I've heard enough!

133
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:37,860
What kind of son defends
his murderer father?

134
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:38,990
Stay out of this.

135
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,560
Let me be blunt.

136
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:42,960
You should back off, Jin Se Hoon.

137
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:47,130
I was Ki Beom's wife,
and as for Manager Hwang,

138
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,700
he's testifying as a witness
to follow his conscience, isn't he?

139
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:51,670
Please calm down.

140
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,510
Cha Ki Beom being wrongfully framed,
and his death.

141
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,740
I agree it's all a tragedy.

142
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:01,710
But the living must go on.

143
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,520
Wouldn't you agree?

144
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:07,150
What?

145
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:10,090
That jerk. What did he say?

146
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:12,220
Did that jerk just...

147
00:09:12,290 --> 00:09:14,660
threaten us, Manager Hwang?

148
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:20,700
He's Jin Tae Seok's son, all right.
Just as bad, if not worse.

149
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,840
Now that Chairman Jin knows,
he won't stand by idly.

150
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:31,340
He'll find out that Manager Hwang
is testifying too.

151
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:35,880
What if something happens
to Manager Hwang...

152
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,450
I can take care of myself.
Don't worry about me.

153
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:44,820
I just met
with Vice President Jin Se Hoon.

154
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,360
You saw Se Hoon?

155
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:51,060
It looked like
he's made up his mind...

156
00:09:51,460 --> 00:09:53,100
to side with
Honorary Chairman Jin Tae Seok.

157
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,770
They'll do whatever they can
to stop the retrial, then.

158
00:09:57,870 --> 00:09:59,140
I won't let them.

159
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,970
I'll get justice for my dad
and give him the peace he deserves.

160
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:08,610
(Jin Tae Seok)

161
00:10:11,620 --> 00:10:13,720
What's taking so long?
I called for her ages ago.

162
00:10:14,490 --> 00:10:15,720
I'll call again right away.

163
00:10:36,570 --> 00:10:39,210
How much longer must I serve
the Honorary Chairman, Hye Ra?

164
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,610
I know it's hard on you.

165
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,020
The Honorary Chairman
and Cha Jung Won...

166
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,050
are meeting alone right now.

167
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,750
You can rest easy.

168
00:10:57,660 --> 00:11:00,430
I thought we agreed to get along.
No, wait.

169
00:11:02,070 --> 00:11:03,600
I thought we were getting along.

170
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:05,800
I thought so too.

171
00:11:06,170 --> 00:11:07,170
Why?

172
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:08,640
Why, you ask?

173
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:12,840
You filed for a retrial
and have the nerve to ask me that?

174
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:15,250
I see it as the least I can do
out of respect for my father,

175
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:17,080
who raised me.

176
00:11:18,020 --> 00:11:19,450
I think he deserves
to have his name cleared...

177
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,450
Is that going to bring Cha Ki Beom
back from the dead?

178
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:26,520
Don't you find this disrespectful
to me, your birth father?

179
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:36,170
I don't see what...

180
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:40,370
clearing my father's name
has to do with you, Father.

181
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,870
You don't see it?

182
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:46,710
You think I'm the one
who killed Joo Sang Cheol, right?

183
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,550
You believe I framed Cha Ki Beom
for it, don't you?

184
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:51,020
Am I wrong to think that?

185
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,520
You can think whatever you want.

186
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,620
But why waste all your emotions,

187
00:11:56,690 --> 00:11:58,790
time, and money
on something so pointless?

188
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,660
- The statute of limitations is up.
- My point exactly.

189
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:06,430
Even if you were the culprit,
you'd never pay for the crime.

190
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,970
You have nothing to be
nervous about, Father.

191
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:12,540
I'm your father.
How dare you defy me?

192
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,670
If you're my daughter,
then act like it.

193
00:12:14,970 --> 00:12:16,110
Or else...

194
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,110
Or else what?

195
00:12:22,980 --> 00:12:26,350
I was just asking her to treat
her dad a little more warmly.

196
00:12:26,750 --> 00:12:28,390
That's all it was.

197
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:30,550
Isn't that right, Jung Won?

198
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:32,290
Yes, that's right.

199
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:36,490
I guess he's upset...

200
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:38,300
because I'm still
a little shy around him.

201
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,360
Please get some rest, Father.

202
00:12:45,970 --> 00:12:48,610
Does it make you that anxious
to see a father and daughter alone?

203
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:50,670
You're something else.

204
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:54,850
You weren't pressuring Jung Won
about the retrial, were you?

205
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,150
Pressure her?

206
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,880
The statute of limitations
has already expired.

207
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:59,420
Why would I care about that?

208
00:13:00,420 --> 00:13:01,520
That's a relief.

209
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:03,150
That sounds just like you.

210
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:09,260
You're filing for a retrial?

211
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:15,070
To clear the name of my father
who raised me.

212
00:13:15,970 --> 00:13:18,740
Does that mean we'll find out
who the real killer is?

213
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:22,640
The main goal is to prove that
Jung Won's father was innocent.

214
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:25,880
And in the process,
the killer's identity might be revealed.

215
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:27,810
But didn't that happen 25 years ago?

216
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:29,180
How are you going to prove it?

217
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:30,980
By gathering evidence.

218
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,780
Eyewitness testimony is crucial too.

219
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:35,190
And...

220
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:38,320
A confession from the real killer...

221
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,130
would be the strongest evidence.

222
00:13:41,260 --> 00:13:42,660
You mean my dad's confession?

223
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,900
That's never going to happen.

224
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:49,000
It might be possible,
if you help us, Se Mi.

225
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:51,040
Me?

226
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:58,480
What am I supposed to do with this?

227
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:02,550
I need you to ask Grandma
if this is authentic.

228
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:06,220
What, is Grandma some kind of
antiques expert?

229
00:14:08,620 --> 00:14:10,320
All I smell is paper.

230
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,490
I don't even smell that.

231
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:17,030
Hey, on top of everything else,
is your nose clogged too?

232
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,270
After all I did for Jin Se Hoon,
he still gives me the cold shoulder?

233
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:24,240
The cold shoulder? Jin Se Hoon did?

234
00:14:24,670 --> 00:14:28,070
Honestly, what is it now?
Is it because of the fake pregnancy?

235
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:29,810
Is he still holding a grudge?

236
00:14:30,270 --> 00:14:31,410
Not exactly.

237
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,980
Anyway, it's complicated.
You don't need to know, Mom.

238
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:35,480
Wait a minute.

239
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:39,980
What is it?
Did you sense something, Grandma?

240
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:47,020
She says she smells iron.

241
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:48,330
Iron?

242
00:14:48,390 --> 00:14:51,030
- You mean like the element, Fe?
- I'm not anemic, you know.

243
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:53,000
And it's not like I'm pregnant
or anything.

244
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:54,270
No, wait a minute.

245
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:57,230
Iron? That's the smell
of blood, right, Grandma?

246
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,840
I smell blood on that girl.

247
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:04,440
What? Chef Hong,
are you trying to mess with me?

248
00:15:07,180 --> 00:15:09,910
Of all the things to lie about,
you lie about bloodline.

249
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:13,320
Oh, my. Bloodline?

250
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:16,150
Hey, Young Chae,
you're hiding something, aren't you?

251
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,860
That's what Grandma is saying!
She said bloodline!

252
00:15:19,220 --> 00:15:22,130
Don't tell me it's the DNA test
between Jin Tae Seok and Se Hoon?

253
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:25,400
That's it. You are so busted.

254
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,800
- Give it to me. Now.
- I told you, it's not true!

255
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:32,840
That little brat smells fishy.

256
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:38,280
Manager Gu.
Find out what Young Chae is hiding.

257
00:15:38,380 --> 00:15:40,040
- Me?
- Aren't you two...

258
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:41,710
kind of on the same wavelength?

259
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:44,350
Persuade her, beat her,
or steal. I don't care.

260
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:46,380
Just get it for me. Now!

261
00:15:49,890 --> 00:15:52,890
(Court)

262
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,160
(Court)

263
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:04,200
(Court in session)

264
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:07,570
(Courtroom 416)

265
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,640
Where's Manager Hwang?

266
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,780
He said he'd be here in time
for the witness testimony.

267
00:16:14,450 --> 00:16:15,680
Getting started is half the battle.

268
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:18,120
We'll be able to prove
your father's innocence.

269
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,220
Ki Beom will be
looking down on us...

270
00:16:23,220 --> 00:16:24,360
and smiling from the skies.

271
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:30,830
Mi Hyang was supposed to come too.

272
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,660
(Court)

273
00:16:41,370 --> 00:16:42,540
Ki Beom.

274
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:44,780
Today's the day...

275
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:48,210
we'll finally clear your name.

276
00:16:49,210 --> 00:16:50,710
Just wait a little longer.

277
00:16:55,490 --> 00:16:57,990
That Hwang guy said he'd go
to the court with me.

278
00:16:58,420 --> 00:16:59,420
Why isn't he here yet?

279
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:07,060
Are you here?

280
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:10,370
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

281
00:17:15,470 --> 00:17:17,470
So you're going to testify today?

282
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,880
Yes.

283
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:22,880
You're going to bite the hand
that's fed you for decades?

284
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:26,180
Chairman,
you may have been my benefactor,

285
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:27,790
but you are also my sworn enemy.

286
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:31,560
You always told me
to suppress my feelings.

287
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,860
And I tried to,

288
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:36,790
but I couldn't deny my conscience.

289
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:37,860
Your conscience?

290
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:42,130
What good is a conscience?
It won't put food on the table.

291
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:43,970
You fool.

292
00:17:43,970 --> 00:17:46,170
At least I can live with myself.

293
00:17:47,170 --> 00:17:49,240
I'm going to bring everything
to light...

294
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:51,980
and do the decent thing.

295
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:54,750
I hear you're quite close...

296
00:17:55,250 --> 00:17:57,180
with that woman, Jo Mi Hyang.

297
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:02,720
You're taking care of the mother
of the child you killed?

298
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:06,220
- How touching.
- Chairman!

299
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:08,530
I didn't follow your order.

300
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,960
She was a child... How could you?

301
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:13,260
She's dead either way.

302
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:15,230
I felt responsible,

303
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:17,770
so I've lived with this heavy burden
ever since.

304
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,870
To think I actually trusted
someone like you.

305
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:23,810
Jo Mi Hyang.

306
00:18:24,580 --> 00:18:27,680
I guess I'll have to send her
to join her husband and daughter.

307
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,050
What have you done to Mi Hyang?

308
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,350
I have Jo Mi Hyang.

309
00:18:38,590 --> 00:18:40,560
Help me!

310
00:18:44,230 --> 00:18:48,270
Her life is in your hands now,
Manager Hwang.

311
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:02,280
I can't believe Manager Hwang
didn't show up.

312
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,320
Do you think something
might have happened to him?

313
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,350
He's not the type
to just change his mind.

314
00:19:09,990 --> 00:19:11,290
The phone is turned off.

315
00:19:11,290 --> 00:19:12,960
Please leave a message
after the tone.

316
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:14,660
His phone is off too.

317
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:17,060
If we don't submit...

318
00:19:17,930 --> 00:19:21,230
new evidence or secure another witness
by the next trial date,

319
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,130
it'll be hard to win.

320
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,370
Then we have to find one.

321
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:28,040
Evidence, a witness,
whatever it takes.

322
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,110
What?

323
00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:39,120
You want me to be a witness
for Cha Ki Beom's retrial?

324
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:42,450
- Yes.
- And why should I?

325
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:44,350
Don't play dumb.

326
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:48,590
Cha Ki Beom did time
for murdering my father, Joo Sang Cheol.

327
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:50,860
And you're a big part
of the reason why.

328
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:55,500
Hey, I had no idea Jin Tae Seok
was going to pin it on Cha Ki Beom.

329
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:57,170
Then just testify to that.

330
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,670
No way, I can't.

331
00:20:01,670 --> 00:20:04,910
My reputation's already hit bottom...

332
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,250
for being in and out
of a holding cell. Okay?

333
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:12,880
You want me to announce in court
that I took down Joo Sang Cheol?

334
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:15,050
Is your reputation more important
than the truth?

335
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,190
Of course it is,

336
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:18,260
for people like me,
whose business is money.

337
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:22,790
Do you know why I spread the rumors
about being this terrifying woman...

338
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:24,090
so powerful she'd knock a bird
from the sky?

339
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:27,230
Because people fear a scary person
more than they respect a good one.

340
00:20:27,860 --> 00:20:28,870
But...

341
00:20:30,370 --> 00:20:31,670
you know as well as I do.

342
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:33,970
The people you really have to be
scared of...

343
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:37,570
are the good ones, the kind ones.

344
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:41,550
You're sending shivers
down my spine.

345
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:45,820
I don't care about Cha Jung Won
and her father's retrial or appeal.

346
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:48,620
You handle it.
I'll pretend I never heard a thing.

347
00:20:56,760 --> 00:21:00,660
He said that if you testified,
he would go after Mi Hyang?

348
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,100
Jin Tae Seok did?

349
00:21:02,570 --> 00:21:03,570
Yes.

350
00:21:04,430 --> 00:21:07,000
Is that why you couldn't
come to court?

351
00:21:08,370 --> 00:21:09,440
Yes, that's right.

352
00:21:10,010 --> 00:21:11,010
I'm so sorry.

353
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,840
Where is my mom, Mi Hyang,
right now?

354
00:21:16,250 --> 00:21:18,250
He said he'd only release her
if the retrial gets dismissed.

355
00:21:24,390 --> 00:21:25,390
What?

356
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:28,390
Mi Hyang's been taken
by Jin Tae Seok?

357
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:30,230
He did it
to blackmail Manager Hwang...

358
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:32,660
so he couldn't testify.

359
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:34,770
Dad resorted to kidnapping?

360
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:38,800
Knowing Jin Tae Seok,

361
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,070
where would he have locked her up?

362
00:21:41,340 --> 00:21:42,340
You don't think...

363
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,340
something's happened to her, do you?

364
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:47,780
I can't believe Dad did it again.

365
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:49,810
I have to find where Mi Hyang...

366
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:51,780
is locked up.

367
00:21:59,090 --> 00:22:00,460
Min Jung, you don't know either?

368
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:03,390
You know
I can't tell you even if I did.

369
00:22:03,390 --> 00:22:04,800
I may have sent you to him,

370
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,630
but your heart is still with me,
Min Jung.

371
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:10,200
I don't even know
my own heart anymore.

372
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:13,840
Who I am, who I work for,
what I should do...

373
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,540
I'm just so confused.

374
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,510
I'm sorry, Chairman.

375
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,880
It's time for me to see to
the Honorary Chairman's dinner.

376
00:22:34,390 --> 00:22:35,390
Dinner?

377
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:39,500
But we all just ate together.

378
00:22:57,650 --> 00:22:59,980
Manager Hwang,
I need you to get here. Now.

379
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:09,160
Your meal.

380
00:23:10,330 --> 00:23:11,390
You should eat.

381
00:23:17,330 --> 00:23:20,840
- Please just let me go.
- That's not up to me.

382
00:23:21,510 --> 00:23:24,170
Don't make a sound
and just eat quietly.

383
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,280
I'll be back in 30 minutes.

384
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,100
You nearly gave me a heart attack.

385
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:52,700
You're all right.

386
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:55,810
Thank goodness. I'm so relieved.

387
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:57,610
You have no idea how worried I was.

388
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:01,550
Okay, enough.
Just get me out of here now.

389
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:04,710
Yes, of course. You can count on me.

390
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,600
- Mom.
- Jung Won.

391
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:24,300
Are you hurt?

392
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:26,370
I'm okay.

393
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:29,570
I was so scared for you.

394
00:24:29,770 --> 00:24:32,610
I was scared too.
I feared I'd never see you again.

395
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,680
Manager Hwang, thank you.

396
00:24:37,950 --> 00:24:38,950
Thank you.

397
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:41,650
I didn't do a thing.

398
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:43,850
So, how did you find her?

399
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:46,120
Chairman Han Hye Ra told me
where she was.

400
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:53,300
What? Jo Mi Hyang is gone?

401
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,000
I'm sorry, sir.

402
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:58,070
How could you have been so careless?
Go get her back here now!

403
00:24:59,470 --> 00:25:00,540
That won't be necessary.

404
00:25:04,810 --> 00:25:06,480
Did you get her out of there?

405
00:25:06,710 --> 00:25:09,110
I undid your work of locking her up.

406
00:25:09,110 --> 00:25:10,180
Why would you do that?

407
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:13,880
With her locked up,
Manager Hwang can't get a retrial,

408
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,150
or spout nonsense in court.

409
00:25:15,490 --> 00:25:16,490
Nonsense?

410
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:20,320
He's willing to risk his life
to testify.

411
00:25:20,790 --> 00:25:23,130
The man who served you loyally
for 25 years.

412
00:25:23,630 --> 00:25:24,630
Why do you think he'd do that?

413
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:26,830
Because he's
a despicable, ungrateful man.

414
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:30,070
I trusted him with everything,

415
00:25:30,370 --> 00:25:32,740
and he dares to testify
that I killed Joo Sang Cheol?

416
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,570
- The scumbag.
- According to you,

417
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,540
it's not just Manager Hwang.

418
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:40,610
Jung Won, Vice Chairman Joo Ha Neul,
and even me...

419
00:25:41,650 --> 00:25:43,450
We're all scumbags to you,
aren't we?

420
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:47,250
Will you only be satisfied
when you see the people you love...

421
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:50,150
bleed to death in agony
right in front of you?

422
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:51,220
It's not like that.

423
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:53,060
Why won't you even try
to understand me?

424
00:25:53,390 --> 00:25:57,630
For my family and Kunhyang Group,
I did what others wouldn't dare.

425
00:25:57,990 --> 00:25:59,360
How is that wrong? Why?

426
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:12,040
Chairman Gong!

427
00:26:12,310 --> 00:26:13,310
What? What is it?

428
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:16,050
I stole this from Ms. Young Chae.

429
00:26:16,510 --> 00:26:19,280
The original DNA test results
for Jin Tae Seok and Jin Se Hoon.

430
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:22,250
(There is a 0.123 percent chance
of a biological relationship...)

431
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:23,320
(between Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon.)

432
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:29,230
Hey, this...

433
00:26:29,430 --> 00:26:32,200
makes Jin Se Hoon
completely useless.

434
00:26:32,630 --> 00:26:34,200
I have to get Young Chae
to divorce him.

435
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:46,510
Se Mi.

436
00:26:50,450 --> 00:26:51,450
You should take a quick break.

437
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,030
I'll go get us some tea.

438
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:37,130
So Mom bought the same one
for Jung Won and me.

439
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,240
It's cute.

440
00:27:47,900 --> 00:27:49,310
I wonder if Mom bought this one too.

441
00:27:52,310 --> 00:27:55,750
Teddy bear, we're here to buy
a birthday present for Mommy.

442
00:27:56,650 --> 00:27:58,580
Sir, I'll take the gold ring.

443
00:27:59,180 --> 00:28:00,420
Can't go wrong with gold.

444
00:28:04,590 --> 00:28:08,160
- What is it?
- Is this a talking doll?

445
00:28:08,790 --> 00:28:09,790
I don't think so.

446
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:13,760
See? It's making a sound.

447
00:28:18,470 --> 00:28:20,040
My dad bought this for me
when I was little.

448
00:28:20,470 --> 00:28:21,910
I never knew it made a sound.

449
00:28:26,180 --> 00:28:29,410
Teddy bear, we're here to buy
a birthday present for Mommy.

450
00:28:30,410 --> 00:28:32,320
Sir, I'll take the gold ring.

451
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,280
Can't go wrong with gold.

452
00:28:36,420 --> 00:28:38,320
I think my dad's voice
is recorded on here.

453
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:42,930
Teddy bear, we're here to buy
a birthday present for Mommy.

454
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:46,030
- My mom's birthday?
- Sir, I'll take the gold ring.

455
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:48,400
- A gold ring?
- Can't go wrong with gold.

456
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:52,940
That's right,
the jewelry store owner.

457
00:28:53,740 --> 00:28:54,870
I have to find him.

458
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:58,640
It's the only way I can prove
my dad is innocent.

459
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:08,920
(A Graceful Liar)

460
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:33,780
The thing is, Se Hoon isn't
Jin Tae Seok's biological son.

461
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:37,310
Se Hoon isn't his real son.
Then why make him the heir?

462
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:39,880
I'll do anything to make him
the chairman of Kunhyang Group.

463
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:43,950
Jin Tae Seok is Kunhyang Group.
And I am his son and heir.

464
00:29:44,050 --> 00:29:48,990
I'll take over Kunhyang Group,
and I'll decide the succession.

465
00:29:49,090 --> 00:29:51,790
I doubt Chairman Gong will come.

466
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:53,360
It's highly unlikely.

467
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:55,630
You said we must prove
Cha Ki Beom's innocence...

468
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:57,330
to find the killer, right?

469
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:01,600
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
